      "title": "Social media networks and the networks of meanings",
      "abstract": "The article investigates images in communication processes as manifestations of social representations. Focusing on the conflict-affected society of Cyprus, it studies the images used in 76,250 tweets related to the Cyprus problem during the intensification of the negotiations between September 2016 and July 2017. Through social network visualisation, it identifies the most prominent images used to construct meaning about the Cyprus problem, as well as the clusters created through image tweeting. The results show that many images tweeted about the Cyprus problem are institutionalised manifestations of social representations that do not necessarily support the peace process. Instead, they reinforce a social imaginary in which Cyprus is shaped by repeated unsuccessful peace efforts, distant from grassroots society, and by the expectation that a solution will arrive as an external force from political elites.",
